 Now, knowing we will have to put up with the mindframe we came here to get away from, I think we the players have to take these matters into our own hands. Whether it be /ignore, no buying/selling to known non-rpers, not grouping with, etc. there are a few things we can do for ourselves. It's not much, but a little bit is better than nada. Besides, in a few weeks, the only time I will get a glimpse of the PLers is when i see them hawking their wares at a bazzar of some kind,which of course I wouldnt buy, even if I had the platinum.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     I just ask you not to fook the game up for anyone else. Especially at GM events. Just because you can, dont kill a gm controlled character to see what it drops. sit back and let it tell its story.<br>
 Also, on the issue of training, KSing, etc. let the GM's deal with it in game. Warn us here, but dont go on an all out rampage...this action will bring focus of the masses to the other person and be detrimental to you. Look at how posts have been turned upside down and beat with an ugly stick then turned inside out only to end up with a different topic and the purpose of the original post gets lost in the melee.From my perspective flames are a big waste of time.They are like a message written on the bathroom wall of a dank and filthy truckstop in BFE...you see it; might even acknowledge it, but, it's meaningless.<br>
 Speaking of flames, lay off Bane and 1FoL. No, Bane is not egotistical just because he has the title sovereign lord. No, he isnt on a power trip. It's roleplaying. Plain and simple. If you took the time to see how his character came to be, you might have a better understanding. Thats not my story to tell though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
  But, I do know that Bane is a store house of information when it comes to places, faces, and things in the world of Norrath. Yep, I would rank him up in the top 5% of all players when it comes to game knowledge. One thing I like is the idea of a story behind 'norrath'. Bane and the Fist have been searching for this story for quite some time. Is Bane always correct in some of his assumputions? no, of course not. No one is perfect, but, he tries and tries and tries. He will theorize and test that theory and then figure out how the outcome fits into the world. Those actions deserve respect, more-so than being on high end raids.<br>
  I think anything post epic would be boring. Besides, anyone with any sense would know that high end encounters revolve around aggro management and the three minute wonders of the world-Warriors. (defensive discipline)   But, if that is your thing, thats ok too. After all, SOE are the nutless wonders of this server. Yes, I have more contempt for SOE than any guild. With their lack of foresight and lack of enforcement, they have muddied a promising server.<br>
<br>
Anzikon<br>
